
[1]substantial

   SUBSTAN'TIAL, a. Belonging to substance; real; actually existing.

   If this atheist would have his chance to be a real and substantial
   agent, he is more stupid than the vulgar.

   1. Real; solid; true; not seeming or imaginary.

   If happiness be a substantial good.

   The substantial ornaments of virtue.

   2. Corporeal; material.

   The rainbow appears like a substantial arch in the sky.

   3. Having substance; strong; stout; solid; as substantial cloth; a
   substantial fence or gate.

   4. Possessed of goods or estate; responsible; moderately wealthy; as a
   substantial freeholder or farmer; a substantial citizen.
